                <h1>Understanding Biodiversity: Nature's Vital Diversity</h1>
                <p>Biodiversity refers to the variety of life on Earth, encompassing the diversity of species, ecosystems, and genetic variations within species. It plays a crucial role in ecosystem stability, resilience, and productivity. Healthy biodiversity supports ecosystem services like clean air, water, pollination, and climate regulation, essential for human survival.</p>
